    "updated_at": "2015-07-30T08:24:47Z",
    "body": "@uzytkownik Are you talking about `assert!`?\nThat's a macro that expands to something like `if !cond { panic!(...) }`.\nActually, I remember now, someone was suggesting this a while back and I told them it _might_ work, if the compiler would const-evaluate the `panic_fmt` \"weak\" language item and emit a compile-time error.\n\nIt requires the inevitable overhaul of the constant evaluator, support for control-flow (at least `if`) in constants, and running formatting in the compiler, from a constant `format_args!`.\nThen again, the formatting traits can't have the `fmt` methods constant, so scratch that last part.\n\n@steveklabnik I agree, this definitely needs a RFC, although it's likely possible, there's probably even more hairy details than I listed above.\n",
